<div id="review_3535724858" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3535724858" />
    <a title="Alex Bright" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14062167-alex-bright"><img alt="Alex Bright" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627054906p2/14062167.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3535724858?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex Bright" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex Bright" href="/user/show/14062167-alex-bright">Alex Bright</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3535724858" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3742469082800553780">This is by no means a grumpy 3 stars. There was so much social commentary in this story that was invigorating to the mind... but maybe too much. The overlapping of religious, psychological, and technological themes created a surprisingly fun, pulpy mess. I&apos;d say the result was a prodigal-son type story, however I can&apos;t say for certain because in the end I&apos;m not entirely sure which parts were real and which parts weren&apos;t. Think <i>Inception</i>. PKD wrote this in the mid-60s, and I&apos;d really like to know</span>
  <span id="freeText3742469082800553780" style="display:none">This is by no means a grumpy 3 stars. There was so much social commentary in this story that was invigorating to the mind... but maybe too much. The overlapping of religious, psychological, and technological themes created a surprisingly fun, pulpy mess. I'd say the result was a prodigal-son type story, however I can't say for certain because in the end I'm not entirely sure which parts were real and which parts weren't. Think <i>Inception</i>. PKD wrote this in the mid-60s, and I'd really like to know which drug(s) he was on. Certainly not his best work, but definitely... <i>interesting.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="3742469082800553780" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


